The course discusses functional peculiarities of the grammar categories of language.  As a prerequisite for the course, knowledge of formal grammar is necessary.Objectives/eesmärkid:  to present an overview of grammar forms and syntactic constructions from the point of view of the functions that they fulfil.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) knows the basics of functional grammar;  2) is aware of functional characteristics of grammatical forms and syntactical structure of speech; 3) is able to make a functional-semantic analysis of a text.
